items.name: ComfyUI Custom Nodes by xss
items.description:
Custom Nodes for ComfyUI

These are a collection of nodes I have made to help me in my workflows. None of the nodes here require any external dependencies or packages that aren't part of the base ComfyUI install so they should be plug and play.

Installation

  1. Download the node's .zip file

  2. Extract it into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder

  3. Restart your ComfyUI server instance

  4. Refresh the browse you are using for ComfyUI

  5. Have fun!

Let me know if you see any issues.

modelVersions.name: Image to Contrast Mask
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take the provided image and combines a few of the other nodes I have to make it a single step process to make a contrast mask from it. This can be used for background replacement if you have an image with a good depth mask applied such as one that came from MiDaS or just a normal high contrast background.

modelVersions.name: VAE Decode with Preview
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take the provided image and combines a few of the other nodes I have to make it a single step process to make a contrast mask from it. This is a simple node that allows you to preview an image as it is being decoded. It does not save the image by design, but it does output it if one wanted to do so.

modelVersions.name: Image to Mask
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take the provided image and convert it into a mask based on various settings. It works well when combined with images provided my MiDaS for removing backgrounds, especially if further filtered by the other nodes I have provided.

modelVersions.name: Crop
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take the provided image crop it according to the provided dimensions.

modelVersions.name: Gaussian Blur
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take the provided image and blur it. It can be used for normal image blur or in combination with pallet clipping to assist in masking out areas more thoroughly.

modelVersions.name: Invert Image
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will invert the palette of the provided image. It can be useful for creating advanced masks from images or for artistic purposes.

modelVersions.name: Invert Mask
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node will take invert a MASK.

modelVersions.name: Monochromatic Clip
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. This node is great for creating advanced masks from MiDaS depth maps or from other images that have been generated in your workflow. It is also useful in general palette clipping.

modelVersions.name: Mosaic
modelVersions.description: Unzip the contents into your ComfyUI\custom_nodes folder and restart ComfyUI and refresh your browser. The new node should show up under image in the UI. It works great with models like All-In-One-Pixel-Model!

items.name: Caenis - Fate Grand Order
items.description:
A warrior and tyrant who appears in Greek mythology. She went on many adventures with the many heroes who comprised the Argonauts. According to myth, she was born female and was later turned into a man.

Tag: caenis, fgo stage (x)

Like always, I cannot guarantee you'll get amazing results, but hopefully you'll find the model worth your time.

Trained in: NAI

Sample images are all Kotos.

Best weight to use is around: 0.7-1. Caenis is a really stubborn Lora, which shouldn't be very surprising. Because her design has so much going on, it's a little hard to even properly partition the dataset into stages and the lora cook in a way that generates proper, distinct imagery. I gave it my best shot. Not disappointed, but not entirely happy either.

This was all generated via Colab.

Anomalies:

  • Stage 3 is SUPER hard to accurately produce, for the headpiece and the breastplate. I am surprised Stage 1 came out so well, because between it and Stage 3, they have the smallest portion in the dataset. Stage 2 obviously being what people recognize Caenis by, the most.

modelVersions.description: Summer Caenis!

modelVersions.name: v.1.0
modelVersions.description:
Stage 1

  • put animal ears in negative prompts or make sure they're not in positive prompts for more accurate Stage 1 Ascension.

  • keep bodysuit in positive prompts as well

Stage 2

  • You can remove bodysuit and put armor towards the beginning of the prompt. Change up the provided prompt information however you see fit, regarding what you think you can remove to save on prompt tokens to fill in other stuff.

Stage 3

  • Will probably try to redo this one, make it a seperate lora, maybe, or textual inversion or something, I'm not sure. If I don't have it redone by the time I make the Summer Caenis update, I'll probably never do it or I tried to fix and it didn't work out lol

1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 25 images. This time I modified slightly my usual settings, reducing the learning rate to 0.002 after 500 steps (I had tested the model by then and it looked almost ready, but there were signs of undertraining on her skin features and such).

Given the subject, I've tried to focus mostly on full body shots. I think the approach paid off in the end, as some of the example pics evidence, with her powerful physique on display (without prompting specifically to that effect).

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

items.name: POV Triple Licking Oral
items.description:
This is a LoRA to generate POV Triple Licking Oral.

  • I suggest using this at 0.8-1.0 weight for best results but make sure to always play around with the weight.

  • It was generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to activate it: 3girls, triplefellatio, 1boy, penis

  • I suggest using 512x512 then upscaling the picture to an higher resolution.

  • If you add triplets to the prompt - You can possibly generate triplets which is hype.

  • This was made on a very small dataset of 15 pictures - I'm surprised this even worked. It has a lot of issues but when it works, it works.

  • A V2 will be released in the future (no ETA).

All pictures were upscaled using these settings:

  • Upscaler: Fatal-Anime 4x

  • Hires. Steps: 25

  • Denoising Strength: 0.5

  • Upscale by 1.5

Known Issues (As of now)

  • Sometimes - It will deform their tongue but if you add tongue, licking to the prompt - It fixes it most of the time.

  • It will sometimes generate an elongated cock that reaches the moon.

  • Occasionally, It won't generate all three girls but only two but that's still good.

items.name: flowervirus
items.description:
An unusual style that is reminiscent of protozoa, bacterium and virus. Think Disney's recent film "Strange World", the old film "Fantastic Voyage", the Quantum Realm in "Ant Man: Quantumania" but more flower based.

Trained on the base 1.5 checkpoint.

This lora is an extract from a model I trained on images generated in Stable Diffusion on NightCafe. 2800 steps. This is a very strong lora; you may not be able to make every subject "flowervirused". Play around with the weight. If generating with higher steps, increase the weight accordingly.

Add additional emphasis by including the original trigger: flowervirus

Other modifiers to pair with in prompts: geological terms, flower names, virus and bacteria names.

Creates wild things with controlnet. Great for alien landscapes.

Plays well with other lora.

A mysterious fellow in a jacket may show up in your results. He is part of the training images. You can attempt to shoo him away with negative prompts of "people, person, jacket, suit". I prefer to leave him in and in-paint to make him even more alien.

items.name: 100 Face Hassan - Fate/Zero - Fate Grand Order
items.description:
One of the Hassans, the Old Men of the Mountain. Due to the vast variety of skills and the breadth of experience, as well as a mind that no one could predict, they were known and feared as the "Hundred Personas." However in truth, "they" are the result of what would later be called Dissociative Identity Disorder, commonly known as Multiple Personality Disorder.

Like always, I cannot guarantee you'll get amazing results, but hopefully you'll find the model worth your time.

Trained in: NAI

Sample images are all Kotos.

Best weight to use is around: 0.7-1.

This was all generated via Colab.

Anomalies:

  • Hassan's skin tone is strangely finicky despite an imageset that is pretty much all dark grey skin. Sometimes, models will make the skin fairer, either by luminescence saturation or otherwise.

  • Hassan's mask also has strange appearances that I plan to change in the next update very soon.

"wearing mask" to trigger mask. though, given how unreliable it is, you may just get regular Hassan without it lol. try using (wearing mask:1.1) or :1.2 for better results

modelVersions.name: v.1.0
modelVersions.description:
Be sure to remove her eye color in prompts when trying to use "wearing mask" or else her eyes will come through the eye slots. Same with any facial modifiers like lips, etc.

I'll be putting an update out for this one very shortly.

Strength: under0.8(close to 0.8 you will find more mess-up colors in your backgrounds and lose details but better details on character)

Put cat ears in negative prompts if you don't want them.

Fkey has always been my favorite e-illustrator.

I had roughly trained his art style about a month ago, and although the result was very rough and the imitation of the art style was not perfect, I still got my favorite cute girl's face in his art style.

I considered uploading this Lora, but I didn't do it out of respect for Fkey's attitude, which has always been against AI art.

Now I'm more determined about AI arts, and I've trained his art style again, and although I've lost some of my favorite points, I've fixed the very mess-up simple backgrounds and strange lines on the character skins in the previous version.

And in fact, his artistic style focuses on beautiful characters and the atmosphere of the picture but ignores the details of the background. This is actually the opposite of most AI art.

I hope that people who use this Lora will like Fkey and enjoy his work as much as I do, or give me feedback on how to do it better!
